## 📌 Project Overview

A professional, console-based **Student Grade Calculator** built in Java as part of the
DecodeLabs Industrial Training Programme (Batch 2026).

This project follows the **Input → Process → Output (IPO) architectural model**:
- **INPUT** — Student name and subject marks (with full validation)
- **PROCESS** — Total, average, grade, pass/fail, highest, lowest
- **OUTPUT** — Professionally formatted report card

> *"In Project 1, you relied on luck. In Project 2, luck is not allowed."*
> — DecodeLabs

---

## ✨ Features

| # | Feature | Details |
|---|---------|---------|
| 1 | 🔢 Dynamic Subjects | User chooses number of subjects (1 – 20) |
| 2 | ✅ Input Validation | Rejects marks < 0 or > 100, re-prompts on invalid |
| 3 | 🧮 Total & Average | Type-cast division — no truncation errors |
| 4 | 🎯 6-Tier Grade System | A+, A, B, C, D, F based on percentage |
| 5 | ✔️ Pass / Fail Status | Per-subject AND overall average check |
| 6 | 📊 Subject-wise Report | Tabular display of all subjects and marks |
| 7 | 🏆 Highest & Lowest | Best and worst subject detected automatically |
| 8 | 💬 Performance Remark | Outstanding → Needs Improvement |
| 9 | 🔒 Exception Handling | Catches NumberFormatException for non-numeric input |
| 10 | 🖥️ Formatted Output | Box-bordered report card using System.out.printf |

---

## 📐 Grade System

| Grade | Percentage Range | Performance Remark   |
|-------|-----------------|----------------------|
| A+    | 90 – 100 %      | 🌟 Outstanding       |
| A     | 80 – 89 %       | 🏆 Excellent         |
| B     | 70 – 79 %       | 👍 Very Good         |
| C     | 60 – 69 %       | ✅ Good              |
| D     | 50 – 59 %       | 📘 Average           |
| F     | Below 50 %      | ⚠️ Needs Improvement |

**Pass Condition:** Average ≥ 40% AND every individual subject ≥ 40 marks.

