## 🚀 How to Run

### Step 1 — Verify Java is installed
```bash
java -version
javac -version
```
Both must show a version number. If not, download JDK from:
👉 https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/

---

### Step 2 — Save the file
Make sure your file is saved as:
```
StudentGradeCalculator.java
```
> ⚠️ The filename MUST match the class name exactly. Java is case-sensitive.

---

### Step 3 — Open terminal in the same folder
In VS Code: press **Ctrl + `** (backtick) to open the built-in terminal.

Make sure the terminal path shows your project folder:
```
PS C:\Users\YourName\...\WEEK 2>
```

---

### Step 4 — Compile
```bash
javac StudentGradeCalculator.java
```
✅ No output = success. A `StudentGradeCalculator.class` file is created.

---

### Step 5 — Run
```bash
java StudentGradeCalculator
```

