## 🧠 Java Concepts Used

| Concept | Where Used |
|---------|-----------|
| Variables & Data Types | `int`, `double`, `String` for marks, average, name |
| Scanner Class | Reading keyboard input with buffer trap fix |
| Arrays | `int[]` for marks, `String[]` for subject names |
| For Loop | Accumulator pattern — summing all marks |
| While Loop | Input validation — re-prompt on invalid entry |
| If-Else Ladder | Grade assignment — strictest condition first |
| Methods | 11 methods, one job each (Single Responsibility) |
| Exception Handling | `try-catch` for `NumberFormatException` |
| Type Casting | `(double)` before division — prevents truncation |
| printf & format | `%.2f` for 2-decimal output, `%-16s` for alignment |
| Constants | `static final` for MAX_MARKS, MIN_MARKS, PASS_PERCENT |

---

## ⚠️ Common Errors & Fixes

| Error Message | Cause | Fix |
|---------------|-------|-----|
| `no class declared in source file` | File not saved, or duplicate class | Press Ctrl+S, then recompile |
| `error: class X is public, should be in file X.java` | Filename ≠ class name | Rename file to match class exactly |
| `could not find or load main class` | Compiled old/broken version | Save file → javac again → java |
| `cannot find symbol` | Method name typo or missing method | Check spelling, ensure all methods are in the file |
| `reached end of file while parsing` | Missing closing brace `}` | Count your `{` and `}` — they must match |

